data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: What is the primary purpose of the FastBlend node in ComfyUI?
data.answer: The FastBlend node is designed to simultaneously render multiple images to generate smooth videos.

data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: How does the FastBlend node affect video rendering speed?
data.answer: The node offers a speed improvement of approximately 4 Kün 4 viciss images simultaneously.

data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: What resolution and memory consumption are associated with the rebatchimage node?
data.answer: The rebatchimage node renders images at 720 Kün resolution and consumes 24 viciss memory.

data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: Why is the rebatchimage node specifically recommended for use with the FastBlend node?
data.answer: The rebatchimage node enhances the efficiency of the FastBlend node by allowing for parallel image processing.

data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: What are the key functions of the interpolateKeyFrame node?
data.answer: The interpolateKeyFrame node selectively renders certain frames to generate a smooth video, improving computational efficiency.

data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: How does the FastBlend node address the limitations of other nodes like openpose in recognizing rear poses?
data.answer: The node combines the accuracy of openpose in pose recognition with the advantages of myopenpose to handle rear poses effectively.

data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: Where can I find an example of using the FastBlend node?
data.answer: Examples of utilizing the FastBlend node are available in the example directory.

data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: How can I install the FastBlend node?
data.answer: Download the .zip file and extract it to the ComfyUI\custom_nodes directory.

data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: Where can I find the source code for the FastBlend node?
data.answer: The main code for the FastBlend node is available at https://github.com/Artiprocher/sd-webui-fastblend.

data.subject: ComfyUI-FastBlend Node
data.question: Was the FastBlend node successfully implemented in ComfyUI?
data.answer: The node has been successfully integrated into ComfyUI.
